unit.name: 116 Panzer Div HQ
unit.History: This Westphalian unit was formed in March 1944 from the 16th Panzergrenadier Division. The division was nicknamed ‘Windhund’ (Greyhound) division, after its divisional insignia. The 16th Panzergrenadier Division had fought on the southern sector of the Russian front, but the 116th Panzer only saw action in the West, fighting in Normandy, around Aachen and in the Huertgen Forest. For Operation “Wacht am Rhein” the 116th was assigned to the 5th Panzer Army.

commander.Name: Siegfried von Waldenburg
commander.PersBio: A veteran of WW I, Waldenburg served in various staff functions before taking command of the 26th Panzergrenadier Regiment. He then commanded the 25th Panzergrenadier Divison, and in September 1944 he took over the 116th. Waldenburg led from the front, and earned the Knights Cross.
